Description: China Strategic Initiative (CSI):
RDTEN funding supports critical classified research that directly advances the core mission and functionality of
INDOPACOM's China Strategic Initiative (CSI - a DoW program of record). CSI informs senior U.S. Gov't / DoW
policymakers with long-term & strategic insights into China actions/policies across the
spectrum, including domestic/foreign policymaking, political thinking, military policies, economic policies, and
many other
areas. Part of CSI consists of a series of integrated analytical working groups comprised of experts from the U.S.
Gov't
(Policy, planning, and intelligence), Federally Funded Research and Development Corporations (FFRDCs),
academia, and
private industry. All INDOPACOM CSI efforts are overseen by a 25-member CSI Review Board (CRB) to ensure
all CSI
programs are integrated and not redundant. All program efforts are done under direction of OSW and the China
Strategic
Roundtable, supporting strategic competition with China, DoW's top priority for defense planning. CSI program is
DoW/
PACOM's first Rebalance to Asia initiative issue nomination priority.

