IOP:
• Deliver JITC analysis tools to support Special Access Program requirements for facilities that do not currently have test
automation to inform test results.
• Continue to mature our cloud testing capabilities to enable more effective data sharing.
• Continue to build our Link 22 test capability by completing a full Link 22 transmit capability into our JDARTS test tool.
• Implement agile continuous T&E through integration of JITC test instrumentation at both CONUS and OCONUS sites.
• Develop scalable instrumentation packages to deploy in virtual, laboratory, and operational environments to collect and analyze
data from test events and joint/combined exercises conducted by other test organizations.
• Leverage use of Artificial Intelligence and Large Language Models prompt libraries to support efficiency in test product
development.
• Support Office of the Secretary of Defense technology maturity assessments of pre-program of record capabilities designed to
augment current capabilities to counter rapidly evolving threats.
• Execute Radio Conformance including Second Generation Anti-Jam Tactical Ultra-High Frequency Radio (SATURN).
• Conduct High Frequency (HF) radio test efforts in support of world operations.

