platforms into a common computer program in support of DDG 51, DD(X), CVN, LHA, and LPD Class ships with incremental deliveries starting in FY26 and full ICS
delivering in 2029 timeframe.

Projects 1447 & 3357: Supports delivery of AEGIS Combat System (ACS) upgrades and integrates new capabilities to rapidly enhance the combat effectiveness of
Arleigh Burke class destroyers (DDG 51) in order to confront an increasing array of strategic, operational, training, and tactical challenges.

The FY 2026 spend plan amount for Surface Combatant Combat System Engineering includes $524,135 thousand of discretionary and $65,000 thousand of mandatory
(reconciliation) for a total of $589,135 thousand. The mandatory funds support the start of development, integration and test of Patriot Advanced Capability-3 (PAC-3)
Missile.
Development & Demonstration (SDD)$$, $$PATRIOT ADVANCED CAPABILITY 3 (PAC-3) Development Integration and test supports the integration of Patriot Advanced Capability-3 (PAC-3) missile system into
the Aegis Combat System. This integration will significantly enhance the warfighting capabilities of the U.S. Navy by providing an expanded battlespace, improved threat
defeat timelines, and a layered defense against advanced air and missile threats. The effort includes the following key components:
1. Software Integration: Development and integration of software modifications to the Aegis Weapon System to effectively control and employ the PAC-3 missile. This
includes adapting existing fire control logic, developing new engagement protocols, and ensuring seamless data exchange between Aegis and the PAC-3 system.
2. Missile Modifications: Development of a compatible radio system for the PAC-3 missile to enable secure and reliable communication with the Aegis Weapon
System to enable missile guidance. Includes funding to adapt the PAC-3 missile system to the maritime environment in order to pass environmental testing and safety
qualification.
3. Mk-41 VLS Adaptation: Development of a canister for the PAC-3 missile which is compatibility with the Mk-41 Vertical Launching System (VLS) currently deployed on
Aegis destroyers. This includes mechanical, electrical, and software modifications to ensure safe and reliable launch from the VLS.

