A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
MK 6 MOD X Computing Infrastructure (CI) delivers the developmental efforts and prototypes to enable future delivery of Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS) in support
of all surface combatants (e.g. DDG, DDG(X), CVN, LPD, LHD, and LHA). IaaS provides hatch able hardware abstracted from software, enabling upgrade outside
modernization periods (agility) to more ships (capacity). The MK 6 MOD X CI is a foundational element of the surface Navy's Integrated Combat System (ICS) System
supporting all future ship classes. Top Level Requirements (TLR) were validated in the Initial Capabilities Document for the Future Surface Combatant Force. Software
Factory (SW Factory) provides a Continuous Integration/Continuous Delivery (CI/CD) pipeline for software where combat system applications are developed, tested,
certified, and fielded to the Fleet at speed. The AEGIS and Ship Self Defense System (SSDS) computer programs will be re-factored into a single ICS computer
program. Provides rapid combat system development, test, certification, and authorization; more frequent delivery, and faster turnaround of Fleet feedback into working
software and fielding to the IaaS-enabled fleet.

