                                                                                                          Articles:       -       -                 -       -        -
Description: Development and delivery MK 6 MOD X Computing Infrastructure (CI) and Infrastructure as a
Service Ordnance Alteration (ORDALT) kits to MK 6 MOD 0 and MOD 1 Ships. The MK 6 MOD X, MK 6 MOD
0 and MOD 1 IaaS ORDALT kits are foundational elements of the surface Navy's efforts to achieve CI/CD and
supports all future ship classes. MK 6 MOD X replaces legacy Combat System hardware configurations enabling
continuous hardware upgrades to deliver improved capability to the Fleet pier side (no hull cuts or dry docks
required) resulting in faster delivery to more platforms. The MK 6 MOD 0 IaaS ORDALT Kit has been developed
and successfully fielded on DDG 81, 123 and 125. The MK 6 MOD 1 IaaS ORDALT Kit has been developed
and successfully fielded on DDG 82, 90, 91, 94, and 128. These ORDALT kits enable the rapid fielding of
capability to these platforms at the speed of relevance.

FY 2026 Plans:
Computing Infrastructure Deliveries for AEGIS (FY26) and SSDS (FY26)
Continued Platforms GFI Deliveries in support of various AEGIS and SSDS Ships

