Note
Specific Project Changes for FY27 from FY26 are summarized below:
Increases:
1. Patriot Advanced Capability - 3 (PAC-3) will increase to support and maintain program schedule required to update missile design, update Vertical Launcher System
(VLS) hardware and software, and complete Combat System changes to integrate.
2. BL 9 DESTROYER CONTINUOUS WARFIGHTING IMPROVEMENTS increases to allow for continued development and integration of new warfighting improvements
required to ensure AEGIS and ICS platforms continue to pace the threats.
Decreases:
1. AEGIS DEVELOPMENT SUPPORT will decrease due to reduced number of developmental baselines.
2. BL 10 AEGIS FLT IIA & III DESTROYER CONTINUOUS WARFIGHTER IMPROVEMENTS will decrease as scope shifts from 3 major efforts (BL 10.0 / BL 10.1 and
BL 10M) to 2 (BL 10.1 / BL 10M).
3. BL 5/7 DESTROYER UPGRADES will decrease as scope is reduced to address critical warfighting improvements and updates required to address deficiencies
identified through continued testing.

A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
AEGIS Development Support is the foundation that maintains the Research and Development Land Based Test Facilities, Technical Design Agent (TDA), Commercial
Off The Shelf (COTS) hardware engineering, and Program Management services required to support the development and integration efforts required to effectively
design, test and certify, Combat System computer programs. Starting in FY26, this line includes the Combat System Test Bed (CSTB) efforts, which support model
