A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This Project develops, demonstrates, and transitions Human Effectiveness technologies required for Department of the Air Force (DAF) warfighters to win future wars
through enabling, augmenting and protecting warfighter performance.

 This project demonstrates technologies to predict, evaluate, and mitigate the effects of novel weapon systems on personnel and mission performance, and exploits
 the offensive capabilities of directed energy systems, developing modeling and simulation tools to unite bioeffects and human performance models from across the
 Department of the Air Force (DAF) in support of Digital Transformation initiatives.

 In addition, this Project develops, demonstrates, and prepares for transition technologies that provide Airman-integrated capabilities to sustain, enhance, and
 augment airmen physical and cognitive performance under challenging and adverse operational and training mission environments; maturing technologies to provide
 commanders real time status monitoring and assessment of individual's mission ready status and intervention protocols to accelerate restoral to combat readiness.

 Further, this Project develops, demonstrates, and transitions advanced training, simulation, mission rehearsal, and other performance-aiding methods and technologies
 to enhance warfighter readiness focusing on integrated high-fidelity weapon systems training technologies; tailored immersive simulation environments for airmen at the
 tactical and operational levels; and incorporation of performance assessment and feedback tools.

 Finally, this Project develops, demonstrates, and readies the transition of technologies to revolutionize the way airmen optimize multi-Unmanned Aerial Vehicle,
 Battle Management Command and Control, Command, Control, Communications and Battle Management, and intel analysis capabilities of DAF systems, including
 autonomous machines, and adaptive teams of Airmen and machines.

 In FY 2027, within Program Element 0603456F/Human Effectiveness Advanced Technology Development, all associated efforts and activities previously reported
 and funded in the following Projects:, 635324/Biosciences Performance Demonstration, 635325/Mission Effective Performance, and 635327/Warfighter Interfaces,
 were transferred to this Project to provide Congress with improved understanding and traceability of the discrete Human Effectiveness technology areas in Research,
 Development, Test & Evaluation (RDT&E), Air Force, Budget Activity (BA) 3.

