B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                    FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
Develop and demonstrate advanced prototype products that provide Airman-integrated technologies providing decision advantage
and enable Department of the Air Force (DAF) warfighter performance under cognitive and physiological stressors associated
with prolonged, high tempo, and demanding mission scenarios as well as stressors associated with operations in adverse
environments (i.e. high altitude, Arctic). Provide technology to real-time assess the physical and cognitive state of warfighters
and provide feedback and intervention capabilities to restore and enhance warfighter performance. This leverages cutting-edge
biosensors, bioinformatics, and artificial intelligence technology to enable faster and more effective performance interventions for
the modern warfighter.

FY 2026 Plans:
In FY 2025 and FY 2026, the Biotechnology for Performance Research and Demonstration effort and funding were reported
in Program Element 0603456F/ Human Effectiveness Advanced Technology Development Project 635324 / Biosciences
Performance Demonstration. FY 2025 funding was $2.763 million, and FY 2026 funding is $4.167 million.
FY 2027 Plans:
-Continue development of physio-cognitive state prototype system by executing high-altitude chamber and centrifuge testing to
validate AI-enabled state assessment for aircrew.
-Complete system development of the Fatigue Optimized Cognition Under Stress (FOCUS) fatigue Management system,
delivering final data analysis, lessons learned, and identifying future transition opportunities with AFRL and other customers.
-Complete the transcutaneous vagal nerve stimulation (tVNS) fatigue countermeasure demonstration, delivering final test results,
lessons learned, and user documentation to prepare for transition to DoW users.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2027 funding increased compared to FY 2026 by $2.290 million due to the transfer of the Biotechnology for Performance
Research and Demonstration effort and associated funding within this Program Element from Project 635324/Biosciences
Performance Demonstration to Project 635323/ Human Effectiveness Technology Demonstration. However, the overall funding
for the Biotechnology for Performance Research and Demonstration effort decreased from FY 2026 by $1.877 million due to
completion of three major activities: integration of eye-tracking fatigue assessment algorithm, development of secure, cloud-based
data system for in-flight physiological data, and development of Airmen/Aircrew fatigue management system. This reduction
also reflects programmatic adjustments to the DAF Science and Technology portfolio for strategic realignment to optimize core
research areas and improve resource efficiency.
