A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This Project develops and demonstrates integrated, state of the art, high energy laser (HEL) weapon demonstrator systems to satisfy Department of the Air Force
requirements in areas including, counter unmanned aerial systems (c-UAS), counter intelligence/surveillance/reconnaissance (c-ISR), and counter missiles (c-Missile)
for High Value Airborne Asset (HVAA) protection and point defense.

In addition, this Project develops and demonstrates high power microwave and other unconventional electromagnetic field generation and transmission technologies that
can be integrated into future weapon systems to support a wide range of the Department of the Air Force missions such as air base defense or the damage/destruction
of an adversary's electronic infrastructure. It also provides inputs to the susceptibility, vulnerability, and lethality databases used across the Department of War to
