0603605F / Advanced Weapons Technology, Project 633152 / High Power Microwave Development and Integration. FY 2025
funding was $27.161 million and FY 2026 funding is $16.783 million.
FY 2027 Plans:
- Complete base defense demonstrations of Directed Energy Frontline Electromagnetic Neutralization and Defeat (DEFEND)
system in collaboration with the Navy. Activities include: Demonstrating of full kill chain in testing; Work with warfighters to develop
CONOPS, CONEMPS, and TTPs.
- Continue design effort of airborne HPM systems. This work will focus on the counter missile and counter unmanned aerial
systems (c-UAS) mission. Activities include: conformal antenna design, build, and test; HPM source packaging to reduce size, and
