on reducing the size of systems to maintain lethality while obtaining compliance with the Air Force Agile Combat Employment
doctrine. The objective is to meet the lethality and capability of DEFEND in 33% of the footprint.
- Commence development of a fully mobile, fire-on-the-move counter-UAS HPM capability. Activities include: HPM integration into
a vehicle platform.
- Commence live operational baselining of counter-UAS. Activities include: Deploying additional system; transitioning system out
of the lab to a program executive office.
